    <insight xml:id="auto_5ccu8yk0">
         <p xml:id="auto_zzqcun65">
            <term>A velocity-time graph</term> is a graph that shows how an object's velocity (speed with direction) changes over time.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_cy5qgbre">
            A velocity-time graph displays velocity on the y-axis and time on the x-axis, where the slope indicates acceleration and the area under the graph represents displacement. 
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_wlkjkyzo">
            A horizontal line signifies constant velocity, an upward slope indicates acceleration, a downward slope indicates deceleration, and a line at zero velocity means the object is stationary.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_lj58zgq4">
            <term>Acceleration</term> is the rate of change of velocity of an object over time. It occurs when an object speeds up, slows down, or changes direction.
        </p>
        
        <p xml:id="auto_ed4zyxu0">
            <md>
                <mrow>\text{Acceleration} = \amp \frac{\text{Change in velocity}}{\text{Corresponding change in time}}</mrow>
                <mrow>\text{a} = \amp \frac{\text{Δv}}{\text{Δt}}</mrow>
                <mrow>\text{a} = \amp \frac{\text{v - u}}{\text{t}}</mrow>
            </md>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_g0yv9lbt">
            Where;
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_63xzta05">
            <ul xml:id="auto_f0drcjjo">
                <li xml:id="auto_h9dfjwbp">
                    <p xml:id="auto_y18gh8jq">
                        <m>\text{a}</m> = Acceleration which is measured in <m>\text{m/s²}</m>
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_r8z5kv6p">
                    <p xml:id="auto_3fok5wss">
                        <m>\text{Δv}</m> = <m>\text{v - u}</m> = change in velocity which is measured in metres per second <m>\text{m/s}</m>
                    </p>
                    <p xml:id="auto_5njdtrvn">
                        <m>\text{v}</m> is the final velocity and <m>\text{u}</m> is the initial velocity.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li xml:id="auto_btqio56q">
                    <p xml:id="auto_bm44x7kg">
                        <m>Δt</m> = <m>\text{t}</m> = time taken which is measured in seconds(s)
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_c5fnns3h">
            <term>Deceleration</term> is negative acceleration, meaning the object is slowing down. It happens when the velocity decreases over time.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_rrgagl1z">
            <ul xml:id="auto_dgh1v6so">
                <li xml:id="auto_4ojyfdcn">
                    <p xml:id="auto_s1ay86sm">
                        In a velocity-time graph, deceleration appears as a downward-sloping line.
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </p>
    </insight>
   
