    <example xml:id="auto_vr1i22ng">
        <statement>
            <p xml:id="auto_yxpttyt3">
                A car starts from rest and accelerates to a velocity of <m>40 \, \text{ m/s}</m> in <m>10 \,\text{ seconds}</m> . It then maintains this velocity for <m>15 \,\text{ seconds}</m> before decelerating to rest, with the total time of motion being <m>45 \,\text{ seconds}</m>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_f5doi3fl">
                <ol xml:id="auto_gh5a8ksf" marker="a)">
                    <li xml:id="auto_2ql70q5s">
                        <p xml:id="auto_ov762wkh">
                            Draw the velocity-time graph to represent its motion.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_x2e8dgdh">
                        <p xml:id="auto_hh4v5zy1">
                            Find the total distance covered.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_4hyz695y">
                        <p xml:id="auto_9lbvvccq">
                            Determine the average velocity.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_6iio9v5m">
                        <p xml:id="auto_rjlfpelk">
                            Calculate the acceleration and deceleration.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p xml:id="auto_2niizqvy">
                <ol xml:id="auto_n0e7v6ke" marker="a)">
                    <li xml:id="auto_8zgtve6v">
                        <p xml:id="auto_rzk55ubf">
                            The velocity-time graph;
                        </p>
                        <image width="60%">
                            <latex-image label = "Velocity2">
                                \begin{tikzpicture}
                                    % Draw fine grid (10x smaller squares)
                                    \draw[gray!30, very thin, step=0.1] (0,0) grid (10,5);
                                    
                                    % Draw main grid
                                    \draw[gray!70, thin, step=1] (0,0) grid (10,5);
                                    
                                    % Axes
                                    \draw[thick,->] (0,0) -- (10,0);
                                    \draw[thick,->] (0,0) -- (0,5);
                                    \node[above, rotate=90] at (-0.8,2) {\textbf {Velocity (m/s)}};
                                    \node[below] at (4.5,-0.4) {\textbf{Time (seconds)}};
                                    
                                    % Y-axis labels (velocity)
                                    \foreach \y in {10,20,30,40}
                                        \draw (-0.2,\y/10) -- (0.2,\y/10) node[left=7pt] {\y};
                                    
                                    % X-axis labels (time)
                                    \foreach \x in {10,20,30,40,45}
                                        \draw (\x/5,-0.2) -- (\x/5,0.2) node[below=7pt] {\x};
                                    
                                    % Graph Title
                                    \node[above] at (4.5,5) {\textbf{Velocity-Time Graph}};
                                    
                                    % Velocity-time graph
                                    \draw[thick,black] (0,0) -- (2,4);  % Acceleration phase (0 to 10s, 0 to 40 m/s)
                                    \draw[thick,black] (2,4) -- (5,4);  % Constant velocity (10s to 25s, 40 m/s)
                                    \draw[thick,black] (5,4) -- (9,0);  % Deceleration phase (25s to 45s, 40 to 0 m/s)
                                    
                                    % Points at key moments
                                    \fill (2,4) circle (2pt);
                                    \fill (5,4) circle (2pt);
                                    \fill (9,0) circle (2pt);
                                    
                                    % Dashed lines for reference
                                    \draw[black, dashed] (2,4) -- (0,4);
                                    \draw[black, dashed] (5,4) -- (0,4);
                                    \draw[black, dashed] (9,0) -- (0,0);
                                    \draw[black, dashed] (2,4) -- (2,0);
                                    \draw[black, dashed] (5,4) -- (5,0);
                                    \draw[black, dashed] (9,0) -- (9,0);
                                \end{tikzpicture}
                            </latex-image>
                        </image>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_lwz5ebhs">
                        <p xml:id="auto_x93jya2a">
                            The total distance is the area under the velocity-time graph, which consists of a trapezium.
                        </p>
                        <p xml:id="auto_eta559qt">
                            <ul xml:id="auto_9n82w2vw">
                                <li xml:id="auto_b5nkwyok">
                                    <p xml:id="auto_1x8i1rql">
                                        Distance during acceleration (triangle).
                                    </p>
                                    <p xml:id="auto_ze0u5nbd">
                                        <md>
                                            <mrow>\text{Area} = \amp \frac{1}{2}\times \text{ base}\times \text{ height}</mrow>
                                            <mrow> \amp \frac{1}{2} \times 10 \times 40</mrow>
                                            <mrow>= \amp 200 \,\text{ m}</mrow>
                                        </md>
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                <li xml:id="auto_rjvmjkyf">
                                    <p xml:id="auto_6lo39pun">
                                        Distance during constant velocity (rectangle)
                                    </p>
                                    <p xml:id="auto_9p34jork">
                                    <md>
                                        <mrow>\text{Area} = \text{base} \times \text{ height}\amp </mrow>
                                        <mrow> \amp 15 \times 40</mrow>
                                        <mrow>=  \amp 600 \,\text{ m}</mrow>
                                    </md>
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                <li xml:id="auto_v7lbtles">
                                    <p xml:id="auto_mldnm8cu">
                                        Distance during deceleration (triangle)
                                    </p>
                                    <p xml:id="auto_hz11og29">
                                        <md>
                                            <mrow>\text{Area} = \amp \frac{1}{2}\times \text{ base}\times \text{ height}</mrow>
                                            <mrow> \amp 20 \times 40</mrow>
                                            <mrow>=  \amp 400\,\text{ m}</mrow>
                                        </md>
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                <li xml:id="auto_k141t886">
                                    <p xml:id="auto_fhnrihmb">
                                        Total distance:
                                    </p>
                                    <p xml:id="auto_mfvbu8vx">
                                        <m>200+600+400</m> = <m>1200\,\text{ m}</m>
                                    </p>
                                    <p xml:id="auto_pgfh3q74">
                                        Therefore, the total distance is <m>1200\,\text{ m}</m>
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_l81210ur">
                        <p xml:id="auto_kmehz6tm">
                            Average Velocity
                        </p>
                        <p xml:id="auto_lb2utiu2">
                            <md>
                                <mrow>\text{Average velocity} = \amp \frac{\text{Total distance}}{\text{ Total time}}</mrow>
                                <mrow> =  \amp \frac{1200}{45}</mrow>
                                <mrow> \amp = 26.67\,\text{ m/s}</mrow>
                            </md>
                        </p>
                        <p xml:id="auto_btrnrhuk">
                            Therefore, the average velocity is <m>26.67\,\text{ m/s}</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_awyn9wzl">
                        <p xml:id="auto_rslyckox">
                            Acceleration and Deceleration
                        </p>
                        <p xml:id="auto_fj52fa6l">
                            Using the equation:
                        </p>
                        <p xml:id="auto_zoao0q3s">
                            <md>
                                <mrow>\text{a} = \amp \frac{\text{v - u}}{\text{t}}</mrow>
                            </md>
                        </p>
                        <p xml:id="auto_1i7nlrlp">
                            Where;
                        </p>
                        <p xml:id="auto_6bpgci2o">
                            <m>\text{v}</m> = is the final velocity (<m>40 \, \text{ m/s}</m>, from the graph)
                        </p>
                        <p xml:id="auto_kl7e5s5a">
                            <m>\text{u}</m> = is the initial velocity (<m>0 \, \text{ m/s}</m>)
                        </p>
                        <p xml:id="auto_dnfjc0y2">
                            <m>\text{t}</m> = is the time taken during acceleration (<m>10 \, \text{ seconds}</m>).
                        </p>
                        <p xml:id="auto_dhs2myec">
                            <md>
                                <mrow> \amp \frac{40 - 0}{10}</mrow>
                                <mrow>= \amp 4 \,\text{ m/s²}</mrow>
                            </md>
                        </p>
                        <p xml:id="auto_psbtjc6o">
                            Therefore, acceleration is <m>4 \,\text{ m/s²}</m>
                        </p>
                        <p xml:id="auto_u963e761">
                            Under deceleration;
                        </p>
                        <p xml:id="auto_9xgsk2vk">
                            <m>\text{v}</m> is the final velocity (<m>0 \, \text{ m/s}</m>, since the car comes to rest),
                        </p>
                        <p xml:id="auto_wvsrybvw">
                            <m>\text{u}</m> is the initial velocity (<m>40 \, \text{ m/s}</m>, from the graph)
                        </p>
                        <p xml:id="auto_g2xqp0um">
                            <m>\text{t}</m> is the time taken during deceleration (<m>10 \, \text{ seconds}</m>).
                        </p>
                        <p xml:id="auto_t1s5ifyw">
                            <md>
                                <mrow> \amp \frac{0 - 40}{10}</mrow>
                                <mrow>= \amp -4 \,\text{ m/s²}</mrow>
                            </md>
                        </p>
                        <p xml:id="auto_qur0xmo9">
                            Therefore, the object is decelerating at  <m> 4 \,\text{ m/s²}</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
            
        </solution>
    </example>
